      "side": 1,
      "message": "Can you use dirent64 from \u003cdirent.h\u003e directly?\n\nMaybe that’s a gigantic pain given #ifdefs that make it conditional and varying levels of NDK support. Ordinarily I’d suggest to stick a backup definition in compat, but if it’s too difficult to work out the conditions when it’s unavailable, then we can do this. But I’d suggest adding a comment at least pointing to the fact that it’s supposed to match \u003cdirent.h\u003e’s dirent64. And maybe even name it Dirent64 to make it a little less ambiguous that it’s supposed to be the always-64-bit version and the lack of traits-ification is OK.",
